<subSubSection id="57D9B48FFFD8173B6EE3FF14D91295E5" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1F7CE704FFD8173B6EE3FF14D8A196CD" blockId="1.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6EE3FF14DB2797D0" bold="true" box="[151,267,151,176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7B529AF5FFD8173B6F66FF14DBFE97D0" author="Razowski" box="[274,466,151,176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" refString="Razowski, J. (1989) The genera of Tortricidae (Lepidoptera). Part II: Palaearctic Olethreutinae. Acta zoologica cracoviensia, 32 (7), 107 - 328." type="journal article" year="1989">Razowski (1989)</bibRefCitation>
proposed two putative autapomorphies for 
<taxonomicName id="D8C39C87FFD8173B6DC8FF14DE7497D0" box="[956,1112,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Rhopalovalva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6DC8FF14DE7497D0" box="[956,1112,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">Rhopalovalva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: the presence of a hairy lobe situated at the distal end of the sacculus and the presence of a pollex on the cucullus. Based on examination of Chinese species and comparison with characters provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="7B529AF5FFD8173B6D06FF5CDE169798" author="Razowski" box="[882,1082,223,248]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" refString="Razowski, J. (1989) The genera of Tortricidae (Lepidoptera). Part II: Palaearctic Olethreutinae. Acta zoologica cracoviensia, 32 (7), 107 - 328." type="journal article" year="1989">Razowski (1989)</bibRefCitation>
, we confirm that the dorsally directed, hairy lobe at the distal end of sacculus is an autapomorphy. However, the presence of a pollex on the cucullus is not a convincing feature because it is absent in some species of 
<taxonomicName id="D8C39C87FFD8173B6DAEFEA4DE5A9620" box="[986,1142,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Rhopalovalva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6DAEFEA4DE5A9620" box="[986,1142,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">Rhopalovalva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6AF1FEAADE849620" box="[1157,1192,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">i.e.</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D8C39C87FFD8173B6AC1FEAADF029620" box="[1205,1326,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Rhopalovalva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6AC1FEAADEEA9620" box="[1205,1222,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6AA0FEAADF029620" box="[1236,1326,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">connata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3684866DFFD8173B6B48FEA4DFB99620" box="[1340,1429,295,320]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" rank="species">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6B48FEA4DFB99620" bold="true" box="[1340,1429,295,320]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D8C39C87FFD8173B6EE3FECEDB639605" box="[151,335,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Rhopalovalva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocuculla" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6EE3FECEDB639605" box="[151,335,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">R. macrocuculla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3684866DFFD8173B6F29FECFDB9B9605" box="[349,439,332,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" rank="species">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6F29FECFDB9B9605" bold="true" box="[349,439,332,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D8C39C87FFD8173B6FB2FECED8FB9605" authority="Zhang &amp; Li" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Li" box="[454,727,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Rhopalovalva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhombea">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6FB2FECED8649605" box="[454,584,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">R. rhombea</emphasis>
Zhang &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="D8C39C87FFD8173B6D67FECEDE6C9605" authority="Zhang &amp; Li" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Li" box="[787,1088,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Rhopalovalva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulata">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6D67FECED99C9605" box="[787,944,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">R. triangulata</emphasis>
Zhang &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
). Also a pollex on the cucullus is found in 
<taxonomicName id="D8C39C87FFD8173B6F55FEECD83896E8" authority="Lederder" authorityName="Lederder" box="[289,532,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Pelochrista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6F55FEECDB8E96E8" box="[289,418,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">Pelochrista</emphasis>
Lederder
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D8C39C87FFD8173B6C56FEECD90B96E8" authority="Obraztzov" authorityName="Obraztzov" box="[546,807,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gibberifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6C56FEECD88A96E8" box="[546,678,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">Gibberifera</emphasis>
Obraztzov
</taxonomicName>
, and other genera, but there is no evidence that these similar structures represent a synapomorphy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F7CE704FFD8173B6EB3FE3BDBEA955D" blockId="1.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">
On the basis of the new species described herein, the definition of 
<taxonomicName id="D8C39C87FFD8173B6DA4FE34DE4096B0" box="[976,1132,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Rhopalovalva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6DA4FE34DE4096B0" box="[976,1132,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">Rhopalovalva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
requires modification: the uncus can be slender, clubbed-shaped, or Y-shaped (occasionally absent); the socii may be fused (i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="D8C39C87FFD8173B6B6FFE5EDFB99694" box="[1307,1429,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Rhopalovalva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6B6FFE5EDF009694" box="[1307,1324,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6B4FFE5EDFB99694" box="[1339,1429,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">connata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3684866DFFD8173B6EE3FE7CDADC9578" box="[151,240,511,536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" rank="species">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6EE3FE7CDAC79578" bold="true" box="[151,235,511,536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
) or separate; there is a hairy lobe situated at the distal end of the sacculus; and the cucullus is variable, often with a ventral pollex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F7CE704FFD8173B6EB3FDCBD91295E5" blockId="1.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">
As presently defined, 
<taxonomicName id="D8C39C87FFD8173B6FBDFDC4D8499500" box="[457,613,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Rhopalovalva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DB73B16FFD8173B6FBDFDC4D8499500" box="[457,613,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="115">Rhopalovalva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed of 13 species, including the two described herein, all of which are distributed in the Palaearctic and Oriental regions.
</paragraph>
